            "answer_text": "Yes.  And it\u2019s the hardest (no words!) but most life-rewarding thing I\u2019ve ever done. Any time I believe I can\u2019t do something or that I haven\u2019t contributed to the world enough for my life in it, I have that book (times thirteen other versions/translations) sitting in my bookcase to prove me wrong. Writing is my way of contributing to a better world. There will always be haters or detractors or people who don\u2019t get it \u2014 I write about harder topics and their effects, such as childhood abuse or family issues \u2014 But the fan mail I get from kids, teens, even adults who thank me for wording what they couldn\u2019t, or for outing subject matter others ignore or don\u2019t want to touch \u2014 It says it all. When I get letters from teens who wish they were LGBTQ instead of physically or sexually abused because the former seems lauded and embraced and the latter feels like a dirty secret, a silent life sentence \u2026 It\u2019s when I know I\u2019m doing my part. We were all born with ways to add sparkle and hope, relief and connection to this often unfair and rough world. Find yours and share it with us. And thank you for doing so. \u2665\ufe0f ",
