            "answer_text": "Hi Jonah, I\u2019m not a traditionally published author, I self-publish. Originally when I first started writing fictional stories five years ago, I never believed my stories were good enough to publish through traditional channels, but I took a chance and uploaded my first book to Amazon about six months after I\u2019d finished it. To my surprise, I got a few sales and uploaded my second book, two weeks later (I was writing a series). Fast forward five years and yesterday I uploaded another story in one of my seven series. I did a quick tally and that was my 59th book. I have a small but loyal bunch of readers who seem to love what I do and thanks to that, I have been supporting myself financially for the past five years. I might not be able to call myself \u201cpublished\u201d but I still consider myself a full-time and self-sustaining author. Have a lovely day :) ",
